This is the root cause of the problem for `DAOCard`s displayed in the `Explorer`.
When `Explorer` builds, its `FutureBuilder` calls `widget.getDaos()` (line 164). This local `getDaos()` re-fetches all DAOs from Firestore and overwrites the global `orgs` list. Since this version of `getDaos()` doesn't set `org.wrapped`, all `Org` instances in the `orgs` list (after `Explorer` loads) will have `org.wrapped` as `null`. Consequently, the `DAOCard`s created from these instances will also see `org.wrapped` as `null`.

The `persist()` function in `main.dart` *does* set `org.wrapped`, but its effect on the global `orgs` list is undone when `Explorer.getDaos()` runs.

To fix this, the `getDaos()` method within [`lib/screens/explorer.dart`](lib/screens/explorer.dart) needs to be updated to include the same logic for populating `org.wrapped` as is present in `main.dart`'s `persist()` function and `dao.dart`'s `StreamBuilder`.

